WEBVTT

00:01.668 --> 00:03.668
<i>WHAT IS IN THE CLOSET?</i>

00:06.939 --> 00:09.074
THIS WAS HER
GRANDMOTHER'S HOUSE.

00:09.109 --> 00:11.344
THEY FOUND HER
ON THE FLOOR.

00:11.379 --> 00:12.910
SHE'S HERE.

00:12.945 --> 00:14.547
WHAT'S IN THE CLOSET?

00:14.582 --> 00:15.813
I DON'T KNOW.

00:15.848 --> 00:18.484
YOU THINK YOU'VE GOT
THIS ONE STORY OVER HERE.

00:18.519 --> 00:19.719
BUT IT'S BIGGER.

00:21.987 --> 00:24.590
- "YOU DO NOT GET OUT."<i>
- DID YOU MAKE IT WARM IN HERE?</i>

00:29.662 --> 00:31.462
I'M AMY BRUNI.

00:31.463 --> 00:33.865
AND I'M ADAM BERRY.

00:33.900 --> 00:35.933
WE'VE SPENT
A COMBINED 30 YEARS

00:35.968 --> 00:39.572
INVESTIGATING THE WORLD'S
MOST TERRIFYING HAUNTINGS.

00:39.607 --> 00:41.205
AFTER THOUSANDS OF CASES,

00:41.240 --> 00:44.477
WE ARE READY FOR OUR
MOST IMPORTANT JOURNEY YET.

00:46.412 --> 00:50.549
RESCUING FAMILIES TERRORIZED
BY PARANORMAL ACTIVITY

00:50.584 --> 00:53.418
IN THEIR OWN HOMES.

00:53.453 --> 00:56.289
WE UNCOVER THE TRUTH
BEHIND THE HAUNTING

00:56.324 --> 00:59.125
TO HELP FAMILIES
RECLAIM THEIR HOMES...

00:59.160 --> 01:00.676
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

01:00.711 --> 01:02.193
...AND THEIR LIVES.

01:02.194 --> 01:05.230
CAPTIONS PAID FOR BY
DISCOVERY COMMUNICATIONS

01:09.869 --> 01:11.571
WE'VE BEEN CALLED HERE
BY A WOMAN NAMED KRISTY.

01:11.606 --> 01:13.123
SHE HAS TWO KIDS.

01:13.158 --> 01:14.605
ONE'S 8.
ONE IS 5.

01:14.640 --> 01:16.574
SHE'S EXTREMELY NERVOUS.

01:16.609 --> 01:19.612
THEY'VE BEEN SEEING
THIS SHADOW FIGURE.

01:19.647 --> 01:21.097
THEY CALL IT
THE SHADOW MAN.

01:21.132 --> 01:22.513
WANDERS AROUND THE HOUSE?

01:22.548 --> 01:25.451
YEAH. I MEAN,
THEY'VE SEEN HIM IN THEIR ROOMS.

01:25.486 --> 01:27.018
SHE DOESN'T KNOW
WHAT TO TELL HER KIDS.

01:27.019 --> 01:29.422
SHE DOESN'T KNOW WHAT THIS THING
IS THAT THEY'VE BEEN SEEING.

01:29.457 --> 01:32.623
SHE WANTS HER KIDS
NOWHERE NEAR THE INVESTIGATION.

01:32.658 --> 01:35.495
I THINK THAT SHE'S NERVOUS
TO, LIKE, FIND OUT WHO IT IS.

01:35.530 --> 01:38.031
I THINK SHE'S NERVOUS
TO HAVE IT IN HER HOUSE,

01:38.066 --> 01:40.532
BUT SHE'S ALSO NERVOUS
TO GET TO THE BOTTOM OF IT.

01:40.533 --> 01:42.935
SHE'S SCARED.
I THINK HER KIDS ARE SCARED.

01:42.970 --> 01:44.602
AND SHE WANTS
ANSWERS FOR THEM.

01:44.637 --> 01:48.040
DOES SHE HAVE ANY IDEA
WHO SHE THINKS IT IS?

01:48.075 --> 01:51.310
SHE THINKS IT MIGHT
BE HER GRANDMOTHER.

01:51.345 --> 01:53.512
THIS WAS HER
GRANDMOTHER'S HOUSE.

01:53.547 --> 01:54.712
OKAY.

01:54.747 --> 01:57.199
SHE AND HER GRANDMOTHER
HAD A BIG FALLING OUT.

01:57.234 --> 01:59.652
AND SHE HADN'T TALKED TO
HER GRANDMOTHER IN YEARS.

01:59.687 --> 02:02.038
SHE WAS NEVER ABLE
TO GET CLOSURE.

02:02.073 --> 02:05.183
AND THEN HER GRANDMOTHER
PASSED AWAY.

02:05.218 --> 02:08.294
HER FAMILY CONVINCED HER
TO BUY THE HOME.

02:13.065 --> 02:14.534
IT'S IMPORTANT
WHEN WE DO THESE CASES

02:14.569 --> 02:16.369
TO NOT ASSUME
WE KNOW WHO IS THERE.

02:16.404 --> 02:17.901
- HI.
- I'M KRISTY.

02:17.936 --> 02:19.539
I REALIZE A LOT
OF THESE FAMILIES WE DEAL WITH

02:19.574 --> 02:21.239
DO THINK
THEY HAVE A GOOD IDEA

02:21.240 --> 02:24.375
OF WHO OR WHAT
IS IN THEIR HOME.

02:24.410 --> 02:26.578
BUT WE'VE JUST FOUND,
IN SO MANY CASES,

02:26.613 --> 02:29.682
IT'S TOTALLY DIFFERENT
THAN WHAT THEY EXPECTED,

02:29.717 --> 02:32.717
OR THERE'S MORE THERE
THAN WHAT THEY REALIZED.

02:32.752 --> 02:35.754
I KNOW WE TALKED ON THE PHONE,
AND WE E-MAILED A FEW TIMES.

02:35.789 --> 02:37.507
BUT THIS IS JUST
KIND OF OUR CHANCE

02:37.542 --> 02:39.801
TO GO THROUGH
THE HOUSE WITH YOU.

02:39.836 --> 02:42.061
AND YOU CAN JUST
KINDA TELL US AREAS

02:42.096 --> 02:43.427
THAT THINGS HAVE HAPPENED.

02:43.462 --> 02:46.232
WHAT KIND OF ACTIVITY HAVE
YOU EXPERIENCED IN THIS ROOM?

02:46.267 --> 02:49.936
UM, A LOT OF TIMES WHEN
I'M SITTING ON THIS COUCH,

02:49.971 --> 02:53.606
I CAN HEAR NOISES COMING
FROM THE BACK OF THE HOUSE.

02:53.641 --> 02:55.139
SOMEBODY RUMMAGING AROUND.

02:55.174 --> 02:58.327
I'LL TAKE A WALK BACK AND LOOK,
AND OBVIOUSLY NOBODY'S THERE,

02:58.362 --> 03:01.481
AND THAT'S WHEN IT OCCURS TO ME
THAT MAYBE IT'S SOMETHING ELSE.

03:04.350 --> 03:05.817
THIS IS THE MASTER BEDROOM.

03:05.818 --> 03:08.371
MOST OF THE TIMES
THAT I'M IN HERE,

03:08.406 --> 03:10.348
I HEAR NOISES COMING
FROM THE CLOSET.

03:10.383 --> 03:12.388
THAT'S WHERE I HEAR
RUMMAGING AND STUFF.

03:12.423 --> 03:14.359
IT'S STRANGE.
I ACTUALLY GET CHILLS.

03:14.394 --> 03:16.329
I'VE TRIED TO REPLICATE IT.
I'VE TRIED TO FIGURE IT OUT.

03:16.364 --> 03:19.263
WHAT'S MAKING THAT NOISE?
I HAVE NO IDEA.

03:19.298 --> 03:21.900
NOW, HAVE YOUR KIDS
HAD ANY EXPERIENCES IN HERE?

03:21.935 --> 03:24.035
UM, YES.
ACTUALLY, MY SON SAW

03:24.070 --> 03:27.607
A SHADOW FIGURE,
UM, IN THIS CORNER.

03:29.775 --> 03:32.444
AND HE SAID IT
VERY MATTER-OF-FACTLY.

03:32.479 --> 03:34.179
IT JUST WAS, UM,

03:34.180 --> 03:36.849
"HEY, THERE WAS
A SHADOW FIGURE."

03:36.884 --> 03:38.382
HE WAS KINDA CONFUSED.

03:38.417 --> 03:40.302
WHO USED TO SLEEP
IN THIS ROOM BEFORE?

03:40.337 --> 03:42.188
GROWING UP, THIS WAS
MY GRANDMA'S ROOM.

03:42.223 --> 03:43.822
WHEN SHE PASSED AWAY,

03:43.823 --> 03:46.692
UM, THEY FOUND HER
ON THE FLOOR OVER THERE.

03:46.727 --> 03:49.562
SHE WAS EITHER GETTING
INTO OR OUT OF BED.

03:49.597 --> 03:50.795
COVERS WERE TURNED BACK.

03:50.830 --> 03:53.633
SHE WAS IN HER PAJAMAS,
RIGHT ALONG BY THE WINDOW THERE.

03:53.668 --> 03:56.035
UM, SO WE'RE NOT
SURE WHAT HAPPENED.

03:56.070 --> 03:57.269
WHAT WAS HER NAME?

03:57.304 --> 04:00.705
DOROTHY.

04:00.740 --> 04:02.640
THIS IS CALEB'S ROOM.

04:02.675 --> 04:04.608
MY DAUGHTER SAW,
SHE SAID,

04:04.643 --> 04:06.913
A SHADOW MAN
STANDING RIGHT HERE.

04:09.382 --> 04:11.417
ACTUALLY, NOT THAT LONG AGO,
MAYBE ONLY ABOUT A WEEK

04:11.452 --> 04:12.950
OR SO AGO, HE CAME OUT.

04:12.985 --> 04:15.421
AND HE SAID THAT HE HEARD
BREATHING IN HERE,

04:15.456 --> 04:16.890
WHICH I'D NEVER
HEARD HIM SAY BEFORE.

04:16.925 --> 04:18.289
THAT WAS A SURPRISE
TO ALL OF US.

04:18.324 --> 04:20.860
HE HAS NEVER HEARD
THAT OR SAID THAT BEFORE.

04:24.931 --> 04:28.734
YOU HAVE AN IDEA AS TO WHO
YOU THINK COULD BE HERE, RIGHT?

04:28.735 --> 04:32.304
UM, I FEEL THAT IT'S MOST
LIKELY MY GRANDMA

04:32.339 --> 04:33.638
WHO LIVED HERE.

04:33.673 --> 04:35.708
I GREW UP COMING
TO THIS HOUSE A LOT.

04:35.743 --> 04:38.628
WE WERE VERY CLOSE.
SHE BABYSAT ME.

04:38.663 --> 04:41.478
SO I WAS HERE ALL THE TIME,
UNTIL 2005.

04:41.513 --> 04:45.883
UM, SHE WENT INTO THE HOSPITAL
TO HAVE A PROCEDURE DONE.

04:45.884 --> 04:47.386
I DIDN'T GET TO VISIT HER
IN THE HOSPITAL,

04:47.421 --> 04:48.619
BUT I DID CALL HER.

04:48.654 --> 04:50.055
AND AFTER SHE GOT
OUT OF THE HOSPITAL,

04:50.090 --> 04:51.355
I CALLED HER UP ONE DAY.

04:51.390 --> 04:53.757
AND SHE YELLED AT ME
ABOUT SOMETHING,

04:53.792 --> 04:56.494
I DON'T KNOW EVEN WHAT SHE SAID,
AND HUNG UP ON ME.

04:56.495 --> 05:00.399
AND SHE NEVER SPOKE
TO ME AGAIN AFTER THAT.

05:00.434 --> 05:01.833
I GOT MARRIED.
I HAD MY DAUGHTER.

05:01.868 --> 05:04.070
EVEN THOSE EVENTS,
IT WASN'T EVEN ENOUGH FOR HER

05:04.105 --> 05:05.836
TO WANNA BE IN MY LIFE.

05:05.871 --> 05:07.806
AND IT SOUNDS CRAZY.
AND THAT'S --

05:07.807 --> 05:09.740
I'M AFRAID OF, LIKE,
ACTUALLY BEING JUDGED LIKE,

05:09.775 --> 05:11.477
"COME ON. YOU HAD TO HAVE DONE
SOMETHING MORE THAN THAT."

05:11.512 --> 05:13.110
BUT HONESTLY, THAT'S IT.

05:13.145 --> 05:15.181
AND I THOUGHT, MAYBE SHE'S
UNHAPPY THAT WE'RE HERE.

05:15.216 --> 05:16.614
MAYBE SHE DOESN'T
WANT US HERE.

05:16.649 --> 05:18.784
THAT WAS MY BIGGEST FEAR MOVING
HERE IS, HOW DOES SHE FEEL?

05:18.819 --> 05:20.986
AND THERE'S NO WAY
OF ME KNOWING THAT.

05:22.054 --> 05:25.024
AFTER SHE DIED, HOW LONG AFTER
DID YOU SAY,

05:25.059 --> 05:26.993
"YES, I'M GONNA
BUY THE HOUSE"?

05:27.028 --> 05:28.893
I REALLY STRUGGLED
WITH THIS,

05:28.928 --> 05:32.231
AND I DIDN'T KNOW WHO COULD
GIVE ME THE RIGHT ANSWER.

05:32.266 --> 05:35.532
SO THIS SOUNDS CRAZY,
BUT I WAS DESPERATE.

05:35.567 --> 05:39.371
WHEN SHE PASSED AWAY, THERE WAS
A NUN THAT WAS AT HER SERVICE

05:39.406 --> 05:41.506
THAT JUST SEEMED
REALLY NICE,

05:41.541 --> 05:44.894
SO I WENT AND TALKED TO THIS NUN
AND I EXPLAINED THE SITUATION.

05:44.929 --> 05:48.606
AND I WAS SO NERVOUS
ABOUT HOW MY GRANDMA
WOULD FEEL ABOUT THIS.

05:48.641 --> 05:52.284
LIKE, THIS WAS, LIKE, THE MOST
EMOTIONAL TIME OF MY LIFE EVER.

05:52.319 --> 05:54.252
AND SO
I TOLD HER EVERYTHING.

05:54.287 --> 05:56.921
AND SHE SAID TO ME,
"DON'T BUY THE HOUSE.

05:56.922 --> 06:00.057
NO. THERE'S TOO MUCH
NEGATIVITY."

06:00.092 --> 06:02.094
AND THAT'S WHERE I KIND OF
GOT MY ANSWER,

06:02.129 --> 06:04.061
BECAUSE SHE WAS, LIKE,
SO "NO, NO, NO."

06:04.096 --> 06:06.431
IN MY MIND, I WAS LIKE, "BUT,
NO, I ACTUALLY THINK I SHOULD."

06:06.466 --> 06:08.099
YOU KNOW, THAT'S WHAT ACTUALLY
VALIDATED IT FOR ME,

06:08.100 --> 06:09.735
WHICH THAT DOESN'T
SOUND RIGHT.

06:09.770 --> 06:11.654
I WENT AGAINST HER
COMPLETELY.

06:11.689 --> 06:13.539
SO YOUR FIRST DAY
IN THE HOUSE,

06:13.574 --> 06:15.139
WHAT WAS THAT LIKE?

06:15.174 --> 06:17.342
I WAS VERY NERVOUS.
I WAS TERRIFIED.

06:17.377 --> 06:19.510
I REMEMBER SITTING THERE
THINKING,

06:19.511 --> 06:22.014
"I'M NEVER GONNA SLEEP AGAIN.
WHAT DOES SHE THINK?"

06:22.049 --> 06:24.150
I MEAN, I THOUGHT --
KNOWING HER PERSONALITY,

06:24.185 --> 06:26.483
THE WRATH
WAS GONNA COME DOWN.

06:26.518 --> 06:29.421
YOU KNOW, IN THIS CASE,
WE HAVE A LOT TO START WITH

06:29.422 --> 06:31.192
- FOR TONIGHT, FOR SURE.
- WE DO. A LOT.

06:33.860 --> 06:36.912
WHAT WE'RE DOING,
THERE'S JUST A LOT AT STAKE.

06:36.947 --> 06:39.965
KRISTY'S SO EMOTIONALLY
INVESTED IN THE OUTCOME.

06:40.000 --> 06:43.236
WHAT IF WE DO GET
AHOLD OF GRANDMA?

06:45.638 --> 06:47.471
- I THINK WE ARE GOOD.
- GOOD.

06:47.506 --> 06:49.640
I FEEL LIKE WE SHOULD
PULL OUT ALL THE STOPS

06:49.641 --> 06:51.742
WHEN IT COMES TO GETTING,

06:51.777 --> 06:55.548
LIKE, DIRECT, CONVERSATIONS
WITH WHATEVER IS HERE.

06:55.583 --> 06:57.716
I REALLY WANNA DO
THE SPIRIT BOX EXPERIMENT.

06:57.751 --> 06:58.951
- OKAY.
- ARE YOU READY?

06:58.986 --> 07:01.385
YEAH. I'M READY.

07:01.420 --> 07:04.290
THE SPIRIT BOX SCANS
THROUGH RADIO FREQUENCIES,

07:04.325 --> 07:06.357
SOMETIMES PICKING UP
ON WORDS.

07:06.392 --> 07:08.292
ONE OF US WEARS
NOISE-PROOF HEADPHONES

07:08.327 --> 07:11.213
AND A BLINDFOLD AND JUST LISTENS
TO THE SPIRIT BOX.

07:11.248 --> 07:14.325
THE PERSON LISTENING SAYS
WHATEVER THEY CAN DECIPHER.

07:14.360 --> 07:17.402
AT THE SAME TIME, THE OTHER
ONE OF US ASKS QUESTIONS.

07:17.403 --> 07:21.104
AND WE HOPE THAT
THERE'S A CORRELATION.

07:21.139 --> 07:23.742
I'D LIKE FOR YOU TO ANSWER
MY QUESTIONS, PLEASE.

07:23.777 --> 07:25.928
UM, YOU CAN TALK
INTO THIS LITTLE BOX.

07:25.963 --> 07:28.080
AND AMY IS,
HOPEFULLY GOING TO BE ABLE

07:28.115 --> 07:30.767
TO HEAR YOU ANSWER.
OKAY?

07:30.802 --> 07:33.419
DOROTHY, ARE YOU HERE?

07:35.787 --> 07:37.922
"PREPARE."

07:37.957 --> 07:40.392
ARE YOU HERE, DOROTHY?

07:40.427 --> 07:41.792
"WHAT IS IT?"

07:41.827 --> 07:44.197
YES OR NO, DOROTHY.
ARE YOU HERE?

07:47.299 --> 07:49.066
"NO."

07:49.101 --> 07:51.671
IF YOU'RE NOT PART
OF THE FAMILY,

07:51.706 --> 07:55.474
CAN YOU TELL ME
YOUR NAME?

07:55.509 --> 07:57.141
"AMY."

07:57.176 --> 07:59.010
DID YOU KNOW
THAT IS AMY?

08:01.046 --> 08:03.680
"I DON'T."

08:03.715 --> 08:05.751
IS THIS MAKING
ANY SENSE?

08:07.986 --> 08:11.156
IT'S STRANGE.
IT IS A LITTLE STRANGE.

08:11.191 --> 08:12.123
WHY?

08:12.158 --> 08:13.325
I WAS LIKE,
"WHAT'S YOUR NAME?"

08:13.360 --> 08:14.693
AND YOU WERE LIKE, "AMY."

08:14.728 --> 08:16.160
- REALLY?
- YEAH.

08:16.195 --> 08:18.796
AND THEN I WAS LIKE,
"DO YOU KNOW THAT THIS IS AMY?"

08:18.797 --> 08:21.965
AND IT SAID, "I DON'T."

08:22.000 --> 08:23.802
THE SPIRIT BOX SAYS
THE NAME AMY.

08:23.837 --> 08:25.436
IT'S -- IT'S REALLY WEIRD.

08:25.471 --> 08:27.172
AND IT DIDN'T SAY
THAT IT WAS TALKING ABOUT HER.

08:27.207 --> 08:29.876
SO WHO'S AMY?
I HAVE NO IDEA.

08:29.911 --> 08:32.509
WE DON'T HAVE
ANY EVIDENCE

08:32.544 --> 08:35.246
THAT POINTS TO WHO
WE THOUGHT IT WOULD BE.

08:35.280 --> 08:36.647
- BUT THE --

08:36.648 --> 08:38.017
****

08:38.052 --> 08:39.950
WHAT WAS THAT?

08:39.985 --> 08:42.471
- IT WAS NOT.
- IT WAS COMING FROM DOWN THERE.

08:42.506 --> 08:44.957
IT SOUNDED TO ME LIKE IT
CAME FROM THIS CLOSET.

08:44.992 --> 08:46.156
RIGHT HERE, RIGHT?

08:46.191 --> 08:48.094
DID ANYTHING
FALL IN HERE?

08:48.129 --> 08:50.060
DO YOU SEE?

08:50.095 --> 08:52.164
I DON'T KNOW WHAT
MADE THAT SOUND.

08:52.199 --> 08:54.531
IT WAS VERY BASSY.

08:54.566 --> 08:56.600
I DON'T UNDERSTAND WHAT --

08:56.635 --> 08:59.337
I DON'T SEE ANYTHING IN HERE
THAT WOULD MAKE THAT SOUND.

08:59.372 --> 09:02.040
WE'RE NOT GONNA BE ABLE TO
FIGURE OUT EXACTLY WHAT IT WAS.

09:02.075 --> 09:04.543
BUT WE'VE HEARD SOMETHING
SIMILAR TO WHAT SHE HEARS,

09:04.578 --> 09:06.845
SO WE KINDA KNOW
NOW WHAT SHE'S EXPERIENCED.

09:06.880 --> 09:08.078
THAT'S REALLY WEIRD.

09:08.113 --> 09:09.313
YEAH.
I MEAN, I THINK WE SHOULD

09:09.348 --> 09:12.201
PROBABLY INVESTIGATE
IN HERE FOR A WHILE.

09:12.236 --> 09:15.054
I MEAN, BASICALLY
THAT JUST LED US HERE.

09:15.089 --> 09:17.122
ALL RIGHT,
THIS IS AMY AND ADAM,

09:17.123 --> 09:19.659
AND WE ARE
IN KRISTY'S BEDROOM.

09:21.727 --> 09:24.829
CAN YOU MAKE A KNOCKING
SOUND LIKE THIS?

09:30.035 --> 09:32.538
WHAT IS IN THE CLOSET?

09:33.805 --> 09:36.041
DO YOU LOVE KRISTY?

09:38.000 --> 09:44.074
Learn the unknown words of this movie
--->   Skeebdo.com

09:49.388 --> 09:50.423
I'M SORRY.

09:57.829 --> 09:59.363
WHAT WAS THAT?
CUT, CUT.

09:59.364 --> 10:01.167
IT DID SOUND LIKE
TWO KNOCKS.

10:01.202 --> 10:03.668
BUT, LIKE, EVP KNOCKS?

10:03.703 --> 10:05.001
WE CAN'T HEAR THEM TALKING.

10:05.036 --> 10:07.638
SO WHY SHOULD WE HEAR --
ALWAYS HEAR THEM KNOCKING?

10:07.639 --> 10:10.976
IF IT'S TALKING TO US,
IT'S GOTTA BE IN THE SAME PLANE,

10:11.011 --> 10:12.275
OR WHEREVER THEY ARE.

10:12.310 --> 10:14.345
IT'S DOING WHAT
YOU'RE ASKING.

10:14.346 --> 10:16.882
HERE.
LET'S TRY IT SOME MORE.

10:21.086 --> 10:23.289
WHAT IS THAT?

10:40.339 --> 10:41.607
HOLY --

10:45.744 --> 10:47.513
THAT'S FRIGHTENING.

10:51.383 --> 10:53.619
I'VE NEVER IN MY LIFE
HEARD THAT COME OUT OF THIS --

10:53.654 --> 10:54.652
THE MACHINE.

10:54.687 --> 10:56.154
WHAT'S IN THE CLOSET?

10:56.189 --> 10:57.623
I DON'T KNOW.

10:59.491 --> 11:01.794
THIS THING IS REALLY TRYING
TO GRAB OUT ATTENTION.

11:01.829 --> 11:04.696
AND IT SOUNDS LIKE A --
A GRUFF VOICE.

11:04.731 --> 11:06.330
IT'S ANGRY AND ORNERY.

11:06.365 --> 11:08.600
AND IT MATCHES THE DESCRIPTION
OF HER GRANDMOTHER.

11:08.635 --> 11:11.937
BUT WE HAVE NOTHING
COMPLETE AND CONCLUSIVE.

11:14.974 --> 11:16.575
SHOULD WE DO SOME EVP?

11:16.610 --> 11:18.509
YEAH.

11:18.544 --> 11:21.113
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

11:23.682 --> 11:25.885
WHY ARE YOU HERE?

11:28.987 --> 11:32.091
IS THERE SOMETHING
IN THAT CLOSET IN THE BEDROOM?

11:35.594 --> 11:37.063
LET'S LISTEN.

11:41.032 --> 11:43.300
<i> WHY ARE YOU HERE?</i>

11:43.335 --> 11:45.871
<i> IS THERE SOMETHING
IN THAT CLOSET IN THE BEDROOM?</i>

11:45.906 --> 11:47.304
WHAT?

11:47.339 --> 11:49.807
<i> WHY ARE YOU HERE?</i>

11:49.842 --> 11:51.977
<i> IS THERE SOMETHING
IN THAT -- </i>

11:52.012 --> 11:53.212
SOMETHING...

11:53.247 --> 11:55.045
SILVER?

11:55.046 --> 11:57.213
<i> WHY ARE YOU HERE?</i>

11:57.248 --> 12:00.619
<i> IS THERE SOMETHING
IN THAT CLOSET IN THE BEDROOM?</i>

12:06.057 --> 12:08.760
MY GOD.

12:08.795 --> 12:11.428
- IT SOUNDED FEMALE.
- IT DID.

12:11.463 --> 12:12.798
WELL, NOW WE HAVE
STUFF TO GO ON.

12:12.833 --> 12:15.332
- WE HAVE A NAME.
- AMY.

12:15.367 --> 12:17.902
YOU HAVE TO BE VERY CAREFUL
NOT TO READ INTO IT.

12:17.903 --> 12:20.772
RIGHT.
EITHER THEY'RE TALKING TO ME,

12:20.807 --> 12:23.607
OR MAYBE THERE IS
AN ENTITY NAMED AMY.

12:23.642 --> 12:26.077
IT'S WEIRD BECAUSE
WE'RE HEARING THESE KNOCKS,

12:26.112 --> 12:28.478
AND THEN WE GET A GROWL
RESPONSE ABOUT THE CLOSET.

12:28.513 --> 12:33.752
AND THE ONLY TIME SHE EVER
HEARS ANYTHING IS IN THE CLOSET.

12:33.787 --> 12:35.820
AND THIS IS ALL
IN THE SAME ROOM

12:35.821 --> 12:37.355
WHERE HER GRANDMOTHER DIED.

12:37.390 --> 12:38.855
YOU KNOW
WHAT WE SHOULD DO?

12:38.890 --> 12:40.724
WE SHOULD TALK
TO KRISTY'S HUSBAND

12:40.759 --> 12:43.327
